#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an5.99"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.99:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.99:0.2"
msgid "10. Kakudhavagga "
msgstr "10. With Kakudha "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.99:0.3"
msgid "99. Sīhasutta "
msgstr "99. The Lion "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.122, sc1
msgctxt "an5.99:1.1"
msgid "“Sīho, bhikkhave, migarājā sāyanhasamayaṃ āsayā nikkhamati; "
msgstr "“Mendicants, towards evening the lion, king of beasts, emerges from his den, "

msgctxt "an5.99:1.2"
msgid "āsayā nikkhamitvā vijambhati; "
msgstr "yawns, "

#. VAR: catuddisaṃ → catuddisā (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an5.99:1.3"
msgid "vijambhitvā samantā catuddisaṃ anuviloketi; "
msgstr "looks all around the four directions, "

#. VAR: catuddisaṃ → catuddisā (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an5.99:1.4"
msgid "samantā catuddisaṃ anuviloketvā tikkhattuṃ sīhanādaṃ nadati; "
msgstr "and roars his lion’s roar three times. "

msgctxt "an5.99:1.5"
msgid "tikkhattuṃ sīhanādaṃ naditvā gocarāya pakkamati. "
msgstr "Then he sets out on the hunt. "

msgctxt "an5.99:1.6"
msgid "So hatthissa cepi pahāraṃ deti, sakkaccaññeva pahāraṃ deti, no asakkaccaṃ; "
msgstr "If he strikes an elephant, he does it carefully, not carelessly. "

#. VAR: mahiṃsassa → mahisassa (bj) | mahīsassa (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.99:1.7"
msgid "mahiṃsassa cepi pahāraṃ deti, sakkaccaññeva pahāraṃ deti, no asakkaccaṃ; "
msgstr "If he strikes a buffalo … "

msgctxt "an5.99:1.8"
msgid "gavassa cepi pahāraṃ deti, sakkaccaññeva pahāraṃ deti, no asakkaccaṃ; "
msgstr "a cow … "

msgctxt "an5.99:1.9"
msgid "dīpissa cepi pahāraṃ deti, sakkaccaññeva pahāraṃ deti, no asakkaccaṃ; "
msgstr "a leopard … "

#. VAR: sasabiḷārānampi → sasaviḷārānaṃ (pts1) | sasabiḷārānaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an5.99:1.10"
msgid "khuddakānañcepi pāṇānaṃ pahāraṃ deti antamaso sasabiḷārānampi, sakkaccaññeva pahāraṃ deti, no asakkaccaṃ. "
msgstr "or any smaller creatures—even a hare or a cat—he does it carefully, not carelessly. "

msgctxt "an5.99:1.11"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an5.99:1.12"
msgid "‘Mā me yoggapatho nassā’ti. "
msgstr "Thinking: ‘May I not lose my way.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an5.99:2.1"
msgid "Sīhoti kho, bhikkhave, tathāgatassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassa. "
msgstr "‘Lion’ is a term for the Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha. "

msgctxt "an5.99:2.2"
msgid "Yaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tathāgato parisāya dhammaṃ deseti, idamassa hoti sīhanādasmiṃ. "
msgstr "When the Realized One teaches Dhamma to an assembly, this is his lion’s roar. "

msgctxt "an5.99:2.3"
msgid "Bhikkhūnañcepi, bhikkhave, tathāgato dhammaṃ deseti, sakkaccaññeva tathāgato dhammaṃ deseti, no asakkaccaṃ; "
msgstr "When the Realized One teaches the monks … "

msgctxt "an5.99:2.4"
msgid "bhikkhunīnañcepi, bhikkhave, tathāgato dhammaṃ deseti, sakkaccaññeva tathāgato dhammaṃ deseti, no asakkaccaṃ; "
msgstr "nuns … "

msgctxt "an5.99:2.5"
msgid "upāsakānañcepi, bhikkhave, tathāgato dhammaṃ deseti, sakkaccaññeva tathāgato dhammaṃ deseti, no asakkaccaṃ; "
msgstr "laymen … "

msgctxt "an5.99:2.6"
msgid "upāsikānañcepi, bhikkhave, tathāgato dhammaṃ deseti, sakkaccaññeva tathāgato dhammaṃ deseti, no asakkaccaṃ; "
msgstr "laywomen … "

#. VAR: annabhāranesādānampi → annabhāranesādānaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an5.99:2.7"
msgid "puthujjanānañcepi, bhikkhave, tathāgato dhammaṃ deseti antamaso annabhāranesādānampi, sakkaccaññeva tathāgato dhammaṃ deseti, no asakkaccaṃ. "
msgstr "or ordinary people—even food-carriers and hunters—he teaches them carefully, not carelessly. "

msgctxt "an5.99:2.8"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an5.99:2.9"
msgid "Dhammagaru, bhikkhave, tathāgato dhammagāravo”ti. "
msgstr "Because the Realized One has respect and reverence for the teaching.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.99:2.10"
msgid "Navamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

